{
  "texts": [
    "The insurance sector must position itself as a more efficient, data-driven, and customercentric industry by collaborating with technology partners and industry experts. 6.",
    "Cultural/societal acceptance: The effect of digitalization in the insurance sector can face hurdles due to societal and cultural reservations (Burchardt and Maisch, 2019).",
    "There can be trust issues as people may be doubtful of the decision-making algorithms for policy pricing or claims.",
    "The human touch in such sensitive matters would be desirable.",
    "Participation from certain demographics in a fully digitalized insurance can be excluded due to the lack of comfort/ confidence with online interactions and technological illiteracy (Butt et al., 2023; Fernando and Jain, 2022; Leal-Rodríguez et al., 2023)."
  ]
}